WorkflowTemplate.name: Specialist: PreRelease Design Changes & Audit Changes

Item.value:
Change Specialist audits the change to ensure processes followed and makes 1 of the following decisions
- Approve, to release Change - Reject, to cancel Change - Rework, to modify Change - Differ, to place Change on hold

- Users create/modify Items/revs, according to plan - Analyst/Contributors attach Solution Items to CN revision, and completes task when done - Upon task completion Solution Items added as additional workflow targets
Choose signoff team.

- Users create/modify Items/revs, according to plan - Analyst/Contributors attach Solution Items to CN revision, and completes task when done - Upon task completion Solution Items added as additional workflow targets

Task adds PreReleased status to CN and assignee can optionally update its effectivity. Please complete these fields: - Special Instructions - Status of Customer Approval - Date of Customer Approval Upon completion Maturity set to Executing
Task sets the CN revision's Disposition to Approved and notifies the Requestor & Analyst that the CN is approved for execution of the implementation plan.
The CIB (Change Implementation Board) participants on the CN revision will review the Implementation Plan. The task sets Maturity to Reviewing.
Choose signoff team.

CIB members evaluate the implementation plan and determine effectivity. - Write signoff comments - Approve - the CN continues forward to execution - Reject - the Change Specialist will determine the intended disposition
The Change Implementation Board (CIB) participant assignments are checked and if empty the user is prompted to assign them.
Assign the Change Implementation Board (CIB) participants on the CN revision. The CIB will review the Implementation plan. Complete task when assignment done.
Task checks if Change Implementation Board (CIB) is assigned and if not routes the workflow to a task requesting its assignment.

Update CN fields: -Implementation Priority -Customer Approval Required Choose option: - Plan OK - Standard Track (if CIB Review necessary) - Plan OK - Fast Track (if CIB Review unnecessary) - Plan Not OK - Rework - Plan Not OK - Reject

For a simple change, use CN revision's description field. For a complex change, create a Schedule with tasks necessary to implement the proposed solution. Complete these fields: - Implementation Priority - Customer Approval Required
The Change Specialist 1 & Analyst participant assignments are checked and if empty the user is prompted to assign them.
Task checks if Change Specialist 1 is assigned and if not routes the workflow to a task requesting its assignment.
Assign the Change Specialist 1 participant on the CN revision. Complete task when assignment done.

Assign the Analyst participant on the CN revision. If additional users to the Analyst also need to add solutions, then assign them to the Change Contributors participant. Complete task when assignment(s) done.
Task checks if Analyst is assigned and if not routes the workflow to a task requesting its assignment.
Task sets the CN revision's Disposition to Investigate and routes the workflow back for rework.
Set the CIB intended result. Review signoff comments. Poll the CIB members or convene a meeting.

Item.value: Analyst changes the plan as required. Review prior signoff comments. If using a schedule, baseline the schedule before re-planning. When replanning done, complete this task to restart the Execute Implementation Task.

WorkflowTemplate.name: Specialist: Set Effectivity & Release CN & SI's

Item.value: Task renames CN to Released & retains the effectivity. Specialist can change the effectivity and Implements relations. Upon task completion CN & its Implements CR are closed.
Task sets the CN revision's Closure to Canceled, Maturitiy to Complete and Disposition to Disapproved. Requestor & Analyst are notified that the CN was rejected.
